<aside id="aboutme_widget-2" class="widget aboutme_widget"><h2 class="widget-title">about.me</h2><div id="am_thumbnail"><a href="https://about.me/lorenabathey" target="_blank" rel="me"><img src="https://assets.about.me/background/users/l/o/r/lorenabathey_1374870390_96.jpg" alt="Lorena Bathey"></a></div><h2 id="am_name"><a href="https://about.me/lorenabathey" style="font-size:large;" target="_blank" rel="me">Lorena Bathey</a></h2><h3 id="am_headline">An author of stories you love....</h3><div id="am_bio"><p>Lorena Bathey attended St. Mary’s College in Moraga graduating with a degree in English.</p>
<p>She started writing her first book, Happy Beginnings: How I Became My Own Fairy Godmother when her world fell apart and she needed to process changes in her life. Lorena found characters Marissa, Andrea, Lily, Deidre and Beatrice were visiting her and wouldn’t leave and her first novel, Beatrice Munson, came to life.</p>
<p>After finishing that book she was inspired to write more novels and she knew that pursuing her passion was the best way to live her life. So a writer she became.</p>
<p>Today Lorena has written four novels, Beatrice Munson, House on Plunkett Street, The X, and Coaster, Meeting Ms. Monroe. She is beginning research on two historical novels.

Find her at www.LorenaBBooks.com</p></div></aside>		</div><!-- #secondary .widget-area -->	</div>
